        <abstract> 
<p>Praises FMB’s BAAS address [on embryology, <hi rend="italic">Rep. BAAS</hi> 50 (1880): 636–44]. Recent progress of embryology splendid.</p> 
            <p>In work on plants, astonished at sensitivity of radicle and its power to transmit stimuli to adjoining part; such general sensitivity should be considered in genesis of nervous system.</p>
            <p>Feels "malicious" pleasure at FMB’s criticism of Herbert Spencer.</p>
        </abstract>
